column5: hmmm....  We might have to move the posts for the hoist a bit to git that one in the shop Skip...  Michael
Doesn't anyone ever do a recce to see if it's even remotely possible.
I think its been done a time or two , but the darn trees grow ... lol
Confusedscious say, never rely on a map more than 5 years old, the brown stuff grows at exponential rates.
That's a beast! what part of the province is he in?
Nice, I'm from the other end of the province. He has the Acadian flags on the boat, is he from Cape Breton by chance?

We Acadians Ryan are all related but he's not from over that way, he's a D'Entremont and puts in at Pubnico , right now is not a good time for them to have their boats out of the water as their fishing season is either under way or just about to start .
Nice tree dance  my Buddies just put in their new beast in Clarks Harbour, Cape Sable Island- District 34
